item.title: [ 41] Gamers, I originally didn't go on a crusade against Expedition 33 because:
item.description:
Gamers,

I originally didn't go on a crusade against Expedition 33 because:

1. It's a new IP. The devs didn’t hijack an existing one, and it certainly isn't a Concord where even robots featured pronouns.

2. It's not a remaster where Type A/Type B nonsense was injected when there were previously none of that.

3. It's a new studio that hasn't sold its soul to globalist entities like Embracer Group.

4. Kepler interactive, its publisher, is owned by a group of independent game devs behind games like Sifu.

5. It's not a DOOM: The Dark Ages where a feminist company like Microsoft is diluting an existing brand by appealing to the Pedro Pascal, Disney-Marvel audience.

6. It's not a Compulsion games or Obsidian--once-revered studios that have been corrupted beyond redemption by DEI and feminist initiatives sponsored by Microsoft.

However, the tone of the DEI inclusions in the game is antagonistic toward French and European identity.

I can't continue spreading a coherent message if I don't call it out.

Many won't agree with this, but we can't keep tolerating every single disrespect to Western identity in the form of 'alternate worlds'.

If you want to do an alternate world, don't use La Tour Eiffel or L'Arc Du Triomphe as your setting only to turn it into South of Midnight.

Expedition 33 is no better in that regard than woke slop like Bridgerton.

The game is beautiful, its art direction is breathtaking, it is definitely a promising future for Western development, but the sneaky DEI pandering ruins the experience.

DEI destroys everything.

Western gaming deserves respect.

European history deserves respect.

Western civilization deserves respect.

item.title: [154] Oblivion Remastered - Good??
item.description:
Never played this when it came out. Playing the remaster now. Why does this game actually BTFO Skyrim?

>actual magic system with some amount of depth
>combat actually feels better than Skyrim? It feels easier to die if you're not properly blocking, enemies actually respond when you hit them etc (might have been an addition of the remaster not sure)
>acrobatics and athletics are awesome and let you feel your character becoming more fit and physically adept as you jump around
>towns feel like they are actual little communities where people know and speak to each other and each has their own unique guild chapters with their own quirks
>joining a guild takes a lot of time and effort and involves a lot of quests that are actually relevant to what the guild is about (ie using actual stealth when assassinating people, using actual magic to become a mage)
>the world is soulful and tranquil, has a feeling of whimsy and serenity that nothing in the genre has matched in recent memory which reminds me of how I looked at classic fantasy as a child
>can customize your own wizard tower and undersea grotto
>Shivering Isles expansion is surreal and feels like a legitimate LSD trip

It's kino. Oblivionchads I kneel.

item.title: [ 74] /sp/ meta thread - anime problem
item.description:
Hiro made it a formal rule that every board is allowed to have one meta thread up on the catalog where people can discuss the board in general. It is not allowed to be deleted.

Therefore, let's talk about /sp/ and a problem I think needs addressing. Anime. I have noticed EVERY DAY there are extremely lowly veiled ‘sports’ threads being created with an anime reaction images in the OP or matcthreads/generals full of low quality posts involving anime reaction images. These are in fact NOT sports threads or sports related posts at all, but rather an enabler for anime fans to post and discuss their favourite anime characters and shows. It is becoming an absolute joke. I am sick of it.

I have NOTHING against anime, but there are plenty of boards available on 4channel to discuss it. /sp/ is a sports board and anime is NOT welcome here. It never has been, and never will be. I would therefore like the janitorial staff on here to start enforcing warnings and bans for repeating misuse of this board to discuss anime.

Please feel free to use this thread to provide feedback, however I must make it clear that if further action is not taken by the hard working janitors, then I may have to take it to higher authorities.

Thanks for your attention.

item.title: [204] /tcg/ Trading Card Game General
item.description:
Mushboo Edition

>I want to learn the game, where do I begin?
Download PTCGL at https://tcg.pokemon.com/en-us/tcgl
The game has a quick tutorial and a bunch of decent decks to get you started against other beginners or against the AI. Some of those decks are very close to meta too. You can also go to your local game store and see if people are playing Pokémon.

>I know how to play, how do I make my own deck?
You have a decent beginner's guide at https://www.justinbasil.com/guide
There's also the old /tcg/ guide at https://imgur.com/a/W4NkOu6
After that, look up meta decks and try to reverse engineer them to see how things work.

>Where to find meta decks?
For big irl events, go to https://limitlesstcg.com/decks
For online events, go to https://play.limitlesstcg.com/decks?game=PTCG
For japanese events, go to https://pokecabook.com/archives/1417

item.title: [178] /out/ings with a pipe
item.description:
Old thread: >>2774508

This is a thread for enjoying a pipe while doing outdoor activities. If you ask why this belongs on /out/, you've never spent an evening by the campfire with a pipe silently enjoying the nature around you, and you're missing out.

>how to get started
Purchase a Missouri Meerschaum Legend and a pouch of Half and Half or Captain Black tobacco, available at most smoke shops. You will need a lighter or match, and something to tamp it with--a large nail works well if you don't have a pipe tool. Fill the pipe with tobacco, pack it down halfway, top it off, pack it down to 3/4, top it off again, pack gently and enjoy. Smoke slower than you think you need to, the tobacco tastes best when it is burning cool. Tamp and re-light as needed. If you still have trouble, try different methods on YouTube until you find one that works for you.

>smoking a pipe will give you cancer
While any tobacco consumption comes with some risk, the cancer risks from occasional pipe use are pretty minimal. Educate yourself and make your own informed health decisions. Some info here https://aacrjournals.org/cancerpreventionresearch/article/10/12/704/46541/Association-between-Cigar-or-Pipe-Smoking-and

>muh weed
Not the time or place. Start your own thread

>I DON’T LIKE WHAT YOU LIKE REEEEEE
Then leave the thread. Pipes have been a part of outdoors culture for centuries. If you don’t like it, leave.
